Welcome to HDSI

"Empowering Communities, Enabling Lives"

About HDSI

“Human Development Society of India (HDSI) is dedicated to empowering marginalized communities through sustainable development initiatives in water projects, education, vocational training, and women empowerment. With a mission to create self-reliant individuals and resilient communities, we have impacted thousands of lives across India.”

"Pathways to Progress: Areas We Work In"

Water Project

Making every drop count! In drought-prone Vidarbha, water scarcity is a critical challenge for communities. HDSI actively digs borewells and open wells, ensuring sustainable water solutions for villages. Our efforts aim to improve access to water for drinking, household needs, and agriculture.

Livelihood

Empowering rural communities! a.

Women Empowerment

Strength in unity! HDSI empowers women through the formation of Self-Help Groups (SHGs) in rural areas. These SHGs provide financial support, training, and a platform for women to start their ventures. With our guidance, many women-led startups are now thriving and inspiring change.

Education

Transforming lives through knowledge! HDSI has planted three Primary English Schools in the rural and tribal parts of Amravati District. These schools provide access to quality education for children who previously had limited opportunities. We believe education is the foundation for brighter futures and sustainable community development.

Geriatric Care

Dignity in every phase of life! HDSI is establishing an old age home to support elderly individuals with specialized needs. This home will focus on the care of seniors with dementia and Alzheimer’s. Our goal is to provide a safe, loving, and dignified environment for the elderly.

Environment

Growing greener futures! HDSI is an active participant in the Green Scout Movement, a global initiative for sustainability. Every year, we organize campaigns to plant and nurture 500 trees in various regions. We are committed to creating a greener, cleaner environment for future generation.

Vocational Skills

Crafting brighter futures! HDSI equips tribal women with vocational training to enhance their employability and confidence. Skills like tailoring, beauty parlour services, and others open doors to new opportunities. Our training programs ensure economic independence and self-sufficiency for women.

Health & Sanitation

Empowering healthier communities! HDSI conducts awareness programs on personal hygiene, menstrual health, and self-care for women. Our sessions help break stigmas and promote a culture of health and dignity. By addressing crucial health and sanitation issues, we strive to build stronger communities.
